HEADWORD: Revelous
<hw>Rev"el*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>reveleus</ets>.]</ety> <def>Fond of festivity; given to merrymaking
or reveling.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Companionable and <qex>revelous</qex> was she.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

